    "description":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSr. DevOps Engineer\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThis is a contract role expected at 40hrs/week; EST hours\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe contract is 3 months to start, however, with a successful candidate, will very likely be extended to 12\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e1099 and C2C\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAbout ThorTech Solutions:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThorTech Solutions is a software development and IT consultancy that specializes in coming up with creative solutions in the cloud, specifically AWS. We utilize new technology and techniques to enable our clients to do things today that they couldn’t do yesterday.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAbout the Client:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe end client is a global enterprise\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThey are looking for someone to start ASAP\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWe (ThorTech) already have one of our consultants working on this contract and the client has requested a second set of hands, so you would likely work closely with our consultant\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDuties / Responsibilities:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eContinuous Release and Deployment Support Services\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eContinuous Monitoring Support Service\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eIncludes modification of application code as necessary\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eContinuous Feedback and Optimization Support Services\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAWS Infrastructure and Security Support Services\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eProvide monthly status reviews depicting performance\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eProvide thought leadership and best practices to development teams\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRequirements:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e5+ years experience in a DevOps Engineer role\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSignificant experience working with Java applications\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExperience with Java profiling/optimization\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExperience with SQL profiling (specifically PostgresSQL)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAWS infrastructure and security support services (K8s, docker, CloudFront, elastic beanstalk, etc)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDeep experience with building and maintenance of CI/CD pipelines\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eProduction experience with CloudFormation\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eProduction experience with Docker, K8s\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eProduction experience with monitoring tools such as Splunk and DataDog\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExperience with Github Actions\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExcellent communication skills\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n",
    "how_to_apply":"\u003cp\u003eFor interested applicants, please forward your updated resume/CV to - \u003ca href=\"mailto:careers@thortech-solutions.com\"\u003ecareers@thortech-solutions.com\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n",
