    "id":"dd0d94c7-9d31-476c-9fa5-add91f6d4ef1","type":"Full Time","url":"https://jobs.github.com/positions/dd0d94c7-9d31-476c-9fa5-add91f6d4ef1","created_at":"Thu Mar 11 10:52:02 UTC 2021","company":"Smart Pricer GmbH ","company_url":null,"location":"Berlin","title":"Senior Full Stack Developer - (m/f/d) ","description":"\u003cp\u003eSmart Pricer is the leading ticket pricing company in Europe. We offer pricing services in the areas of sports, entertainment and ski resorts and are proud to work with partners such as FC Bayern Munich, DFB, Hertha BSC, Sölden ski resort, Zermatt Bergbahnen and many more. Our work is characterized by entrepreneurial thinking, effective transaction management and innovative solutions. We owe our success as one of the world's leading specialists in our field not least to a distinctly team-oriented approach.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTogether we want to grow further and are therefore looking for a\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSenior Full Stack Developer - (m/f/d)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eto support us as soon as possible.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWith us, you are part of a committed and motivated team that rethinks the way pricing is done with a lot of enthusiasm and drive from Berlin. If you want to take on responsibility from day one and drive our mission forward with your own ideas, then your application is just right with us.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYour Responsibilities:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWithin the first three months, you will familiarize yourself with our existing services (you have   access to documentations and team members)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou will lead and own the development of our back-end pricing services incl. the design and deployment of APIs to run our services\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYour responsibilities will range - from rapidly building prototypes in product discovery phase, to delivering reliable quality products in delivery phase, to developing our tech architecture further ensuring functionality, scalability, reliability and security (a hands-on mind-set and strategic oversight are essential for this)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou will define the technical requirements of the company in detail and set up all required processes\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eIn 6-9 month time you will start to build and manage a small technical team of A-players (including software engineers, data scientists)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTogether with the founders you and your team will continuously iterate our product by developing hypotheses, validating them (e.g. through user research and tests) and shipping new features\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou own the operative KPIs tech and will be the voice of tech in all strategic decisions\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou oversee the monitoring of our live pricing services\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eRequirements:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSoftware Developer with a degree in a technical related field such as Computer Science, Bio/Informations or similar\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou have at least 3 years experience working in Software Development\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou are skilled in several backend languages (Go, Ruby) and in working with and deploying cloud services in a Unix environment\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eOptionally you have some frontend experience in TypeScript and CoffeeScript as well as some data analytics background in Python\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou combine a strong hands-on-attitude (and are happy to develop and maintain code yourself) with strategic thinking and an entrepreneurial mindset\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou have a high focus on customer needs and contribute your best knowledge and experience about technology, products and processes\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou are interested in pricing, data mining, ML\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou are characterized by a sovereign appearance as well as good presentation and communication skills\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYour are fluent in English and German\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhat We Offer:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eA friendly and respectful team with a family work culture\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eA great workplace in Berlin Mitte with a part-time remote work option\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe chance to take over a large area of expertise very quickly and to make a steep entry into a management position\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAn attractive compensation package\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eFlexible working hours\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eA secure employment relationship\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMeaning - our work has direct impact on sports and entertainment pricing across all of Europe\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n","how_to_apply":"\u003cp\u003eWe are happy to receiving your application by e-mail, stating your desired salary and earliest possible starting date, at: \u003ca href=\"mailto:miriam.weber@smart-pricer.com\"\u003emiriam.weber@smart-pricer.com\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n","company_logo":"https://jobs.github.com/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBZ2ljIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--42ba9c34dbd16b17bce10dd2e9fff25d2dd68507/Smart%20Pricer%20Logo.jpg"
