    "id":"85f49b29-5845-4154-bf1a-5bf842419f1e","type":"Full Time","url":"https://jobs.github.com/positions/85f49b29-5845-4154-bf1a-5bf842419f1e","created_at":"Wed Mar 10 15:56:16 UTC 2021","company":"Wolfe.com LLC","company_url":"http://wolfe.com","location":"Pittsburgh Pa","title":"Senior DevOps Engineer","description":"\u003cp\u003eWe’re looking for a strong engineer to:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eOwn the AWS infrastructure of our 3 core properties, including Dockerized ECS and more standard EC2 based systems, while working with a small team\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eLiason with our development teams, information security personnel, and card printing facility personnel to satisfy their various requirements\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eUnderstand and act as a backup for the infrastructure of a small manufacturing facility\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWolfe:\nWolfe, LLC is a successful e-commerce company in Pittsburgh, PA.  We are a high-performance fintech and online e-commerce company with a specialization on the $250 billion gift card market.  We formerly owned GiftCards.com and grew the largest online gift card site in the world before selling it in 2016.  We are re-building again under the new brands PerfectGift.com, GiftCardGranny.com and GiftYa.com and improving on what we built in the past.\nAll team members embody our cherished core values of integrity, drive, teamwork and caring.  Our achievements include the first coupon website in 1995 which sold to a public company in 2000 when we were delivering 20 million-page views per month at the peak of the dot-com era.  We then built Direct Response Technologies – grew to 70 employees and sold to Digital River in 2006.  We spun off Jambo Media with our tech team and sold it to Undertone in 2012.  We next built GiftCards.com to 100 employees and in 2016 sold it to (then NASDAQ:HAWK) Blackhawk Network.\nOur in-house and contact center teams are searching for the next top performing leader to help deliver world-class service for our consumer and corporate clients. We deliver an extremely attractive client value proposition in an industry of very few competitors.\nCompany and Executive Team Recognitions:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e2011 Best places to work in Pittsburgh Finalist\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e2011 Ernst \u0026amp; Young Entrepreneur of the Year Award Winner\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e2011 CFO of the Year Finalist\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e2011 CIO of the Year Finalist\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e2013 Governors Impact Award Winner\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e2014 Entreprenuer.com Nationwide Entrepreneur of the Year Finalist\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e2015 CEO of the Year Winner Pittsburgh Technology Council\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e2015 Create Award Winner for Marketing\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e2015 Business Times Diamond Award Winner\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e2015 Business Ethics Award Winner\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e2017 Outstanding Entrepreneur Award Winner by the Pittsburgh Venture Capital Association\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e2019 Carnegie Science Award Recipient, Entrepreneur Category\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e2020 Top 10 Best Places to Work by Pittsburgh Business Times\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Opportunity\nWolfe’s infrastructure is hosted in AWS and is made up of several Dockerized and EC2 based services. We support multiple API layers, administration and partner portals, websites, native apps, and more. Additionally, we have a PCI certified card plastics printing facility located in Green Tree, PA.\nDuties\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHandle the management and ongoing maintenance requirements of multiple AWS accounts along as part of a small team\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWorking with the property developers to migrate current EC2 workloads to ECS Fargate\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSetting and implementing infrastructure standards\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDocumentation, CI/CD, and monitoring\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eOn call rotation\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou’ll also be acting as a backup for the card printing facility infrastructure. This infrastructure is a PCI Card Production compliant network, utilizing similar technologies to our AWS properties.\no\tPlease note: This position is NOT geared toward general IT/Help Desk\nRequirements\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e3-5 years working with AWS, AWS Solutions Architect is a plus\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e3 years working with Linux\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e1 year docker experience\nTelosGifting Technology Stack\nThis is what powers our various properties. You don’t need direct experience in everything, but you’ll be working next to all of these technologies:\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAWS ECS, EC2, RDS\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMySQL, Redis, Rabbit\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCloudflare\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSumologic\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePHP, Symfony\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBitbucket Pipelines\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAnsible, Terraform\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIdeal Skillset\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eProven ability to plan projects, work independently, and liaison with technical and non-technical personnel\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExperience with containerization, application monitoring, and performance evaluation\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExperience with any modern web development framework (Rail/Django/Symfony/etc) is a plus\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBasic security certifications and PCI experience are a plus\nCompensation \u0026amp; Benefits/Perks\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCompensation includes a competitive base salary, incentives, plus participation in company sale proceeds (10-15% in total go to employees on sale or profit).\nWolfe, LLC is committed to providing its employees with a benefits package providing flexibility that ensures a healthy life/work balance.  The great benefits and perks, include:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMedical, Prescription, Vision and Dental\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eGenerous Paid Time-Off policy\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eProfit-sharing (Incentive Stock Plan) our employees have earned over $16m through this program since 2006\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e11 holidays\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTuition Reimbursement\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eEmployee Recognition Program\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCharitable Donation to a Charity of YOUR Choice yearly ($250)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eRefer Friends, and if we hire them you get awarded (up to $1,000)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eFamily Picnic, Holiday Party, and other employee outings\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eOn-site dry-cleaning pick-up service\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eFlex-time Scheduling and a Telecommute Policy\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eNo cubicles, everyone gets a desk\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePrivate Health Advisory Policy for Employee and Dependents\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBrown bag sessions to keep you informed on the company/industry\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf this position excites you, we urge you to apply!\nWolfe, LLC is an Equal Opportunity Employer.\nWolfe, LLC does not sponsor individuals for the purpose of obtaining H-1 Visas.\u003c/p\u003e\n","how_to_apply":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"mailto:jobs@wolfe.com\"\u003ejobs@wolfe.com\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n","company_logo":"https://jobs.github.com/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdkdiIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--ad77badc79a2c42a15179df02e3b0387c666128f/wolfe.png"
